- Verify project structure and files before creating new files.
- Update `_files.md` with new files.
- Check `_files.md` before creating new files.
- Review `_tasks.md` before starting and after finishing tasks.
- Remember, Home Assistant runs in a Docker container named `homeassistant`.
- The project is part of the injected directory.
- Inside the container, the project is at /config/custom_components/aurora_sound_to_light.
- The project is volume-mounted, so file changes reflect in the container.
- Prefix file names with `@` when referencing them.
- Commit all project changes to git.